    <body>
      <div type="page" n="159">
        <pb n="159"/>
        <lg xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F32474af2-eea9-431d-8117-b1b2a3917db9.jp2/1769,909,1748,1607/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>SING THE SONG of men and women</l>
          <l>joined in understanding and respect.</l>
          <l>The song of God&apos;s miracles,</l>
          <l>an earth protected and cherished;</l>
          <l>a gift for our children</l>
          <l>and the generations to come.</l>
          <l>The song of a land once ravished by war,</l>
          <l>now quiet and content;</l>
          <l>her soldiers home, to leave no more.</l>
          <l>The song of a world redeemed:</l>
          <l>the song of peace.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_B" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F32474af2-eea9-431d-8117-b1b2a3917db9.jp2/947,5753,3666,498/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>Salvation is the Jews&apos; victory over human limitations: ignorance or insensitivity. It is the conquest</l>
          <l>of sinfulness, of the evils resident within the self: pride, selfishness, hate, lust, cynicism, the</l>
          <l>deliberate rejection of goodness and truth. Milton Steinberg</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
